==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heliocentrical
<hw>He`li*o*cen"tric"al</hw>
<pr>(h⟦emac⟧`l⟦icr⟧*⟦osl⟧*s⟦ecr⟧n"tr⟦icr⟧*k⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, }</mhw>
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Helio-</ets> + <ets>centric</ets>,
<ets>centrical</ets>: cf. F. <ets>h⟦eacute⟧liocentrique</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>pertaining to the sun's center, or appearing
to be seen from it; having, or relating to, the sun as a center; --
opposed to <contr>geocentrical</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Heliocentric parallax</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Parallax</er>.</cd> -- <mcol><col><b>Heliocentric place</b></col>,
<col><b>latitude</b></col>, <col><b>longitude</b></col></mcol>, <cd>etc.
(of a heavenly body), the direction, latitude, longitude, etc., of the
body as viewed from the sun.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heliochrome</ent>⟦br⟧
